HEADWORD: Bojanus organ
<hw>Bo*ja"nus or"gan</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[From <ets>Bojanus</ets>,
the discoverer.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A glandular organ of
bivalve mollusca, serving in part as a kidney.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

